public Boolean isNode(String id)
, this method checks,
with a query, if the node with the id
specified in input, is already present in the knowledge
base. It returns true if it exists, false
otherwise.
public void addNode(String id, String name, String
type)
, adds a new node to the graph, if
not already present. This method takes in input three
Strings, namely an id, a name and a
type for the node to be inserted. It checks if the
node is already present with the isNode
method, then after establishing a new Session it performs
a query to add a new object to the
database, with the specified id, name and type.
public void addNodeProperty(String id, String type)
this method adds a property to a
specified node, after checking it exists with the
isNode method. It takes in input the id of the
node and the property-type. It also sets the label
of the node to the type passed in input
(after deleting the already existent one); this is
done in order to have access to some filtering
functionality of nodes in the neo4J desktop app.
public String getNodeId(String name)
, this method
returns the id of a node of which name it
is specified in input as a String. It returns null
if a node with the specified name does not
exist.
public Boolean isEdge(String id1, String id2, String
type)
, this method checks, with a query,
if an edge between two specified nodes with the respective
ids specified in input, is already
present in the knowledge base. It returns true if
a connection of the specified type exists,
false otherwise.
public void addEdge(String id1, String id2, String
type)
, adds a new edge in the graph
between two nodes, specified by id, with the specified
type property. First it checks if both
nodes exist, then checks if the same edge is not already
present. If this condition is satisfied,
it runs a query to add the edge to the knowledge base.
public Boolean resetGraph()
, this method deletes all
nodes and edges from the current
instance of the knowledge base.
public void close()
, this method is used to close
the connection with the neo4J database,
calling the method close() on the driver private attribute.
RELATIONS
This class stores a representation of the graph in
Java. By adding an SRO triple, it builds a graph
abstraction, by memorizing the nodes and the edges
(without duplicates). In this class are also
implemented methods to discover aliases (not already
discovered by coreference resolution) based
on the term’s Wikipedia Page ID: if two different
terms have the same page ID they are aliases.
